@lguohan Another thing we can do is to make the interfaces-config service run Before sonic target instead of After.

This will shorten number of dependencies to specify (and to know about) for future services which bind to loopback and possibly fix some existing rarely reproducible bugs like this one. 

From my preliminary runs this approach won't affect startup time.

